@Node Use " -„ū„- A/NES How 2 -„ū„- "


	How to use A/NES
	-----------------
	Well, it's really quite simple. Just select a suitable
	ROM file (press "LOAD ROM" button)..
	And to run it press "START ROM".

	Note! Most games uses a MMC/Mapper chip that is
	not yet emulated by A/NES, so the compability
	at the moment is not yet very high. 

	Many features in the Emulator/GUI is not yet fully
	implemented and will be enabled in the near future.


	JOYSTICK 1
	----------
	ENTER       - Start
	RIGHT SHIFT - Select	
	LEFT CTRL   - A
	LEFT ALT    - B
        ARROWKEYS   - Guess what? :)

	Joystick 2 is not yet emulated.

	Pressing Right mouse button aborts the emulation.
	Note! In it's current state there is no way
	to continue the emulation where it left off when
	you aborted it. This will be implemented in a
	later version of A/NES.


@Endnode
@Node Bugs " -„ū„- A/NES Bugs -„ū„- "

	Reporting bugs
	--------------
	Yes. There is bugs in A/NES. It's just a question
	of time before you find them. :)
	Please report bugs to us that causes your computer
	to behave strangly. (See our addresses elsewhere
	in this guide file).
	BUT! Don't report about non-working ROMS!
	Many things is NOT emulated properly / yet, so please
	have patience...
	Note that questions/problems concerning the GUI
	should be reported to  Fredrik . 

	Known bugs
	-----------
	* File requester sometimes behave very strange.
	* Joystick emulation contain bugs.
	* CPU emulation is not 100% bugfree...
        * The GUI doesn't check if it is active, so if you
          press on some other screen the position can create
          an action in the emulator...


@Endnode
@Node Requirements " -„ū„- A/NES Requires -„ū„- "

	Requirements
	------------
	A/NES today requires atleast a 68020 and the AGA
	chipset. Some fast memory is strongly recommended
	but not required.
	But of course, a fast processor isn't that bad
	either. :)

	You should have reqtools.library in your LIBS:
	drawer to make things work properly.



@Endnode
@Node Register " -„ū„- A/NES Registration -„ū„- "


	How to register
	---------------

        This version of A/NES is freeware, but this will change
        to the next version and A/NES will be become shareware.

        You will be informed how to become a registered user
        in the next version of A/NES.


@Endnode
@Node Introduction " -„ū„- A/NES Introduction-„ū„- "



        Introduction
        ------------


        It all started a day in may in the year of 1997. I was
        watching Nesticle on a PC machine and started to wonder
        why there was no decent NES emulator for Amiga...
        So I (Morgan) and my friend Fredrik started this little
        project.
        We had never done anything like this before so it was
        a challenge.
        The CPU emulation (it's incredible fast) was written
        from scratch in 68020 assembly language and everything
        else concerning the emulation is also written in assembly.

        And here it is!
        An early beta version...

        Altough the emulation is far from perfect, we still hope
        that you enjoy the fastest Nintendo 8 bit emulator for 
        Amiga today.



@Endnode
@Node Legal " -„ū„- A/NES -„ū„- "


 The Legalities of Console Copying and Emulation
 3-11-97, Copyright Anthony DiPasquale
 http://www.pce.net/anthony, anthony@pce.net

    1.  Is it legal to create an emulator?
      There has been some discussion on this.  To create an emulator
    one must have a high level of knowledge of the source platform to
    be emulated, and the target platform the emulator runs on.  To find
    out info about the source, usually takes reverse engineering, of
    the original console, which may be considered illigal.

    2.  Is it illigal to run/use an emulator?
      This goes along with the above question.  There is debate around
    this as well.  The general rule to follow is:  You are allowed to
    own/run an emulator, as long as you actually own a corresponding
    hardware device.  Example, you own a game boy, so you are allowed
    to run a game boy emulator on your computer.

    3.  Is downloading ROM images illigal?
      No, it is not, as long as you own a hardware copy of each rom image
    you download.  If you download images you do not own a copy of, you
    are commimiting piracy.  By now, I'm sure Nintendo has realized that
    all the game boy game roms have been being illigally copied, that 
    being one of the most popular emulators, and they do not seem to care.
    Chances are if you copy a Coleco, Atari, Sega Master System, etc, it
    wouldn't matter too much.  The general rule is:  If the company is no
    longer collecting royalties, they probably won't mind.  Who would pay
    $30 for a Coleco Vision ROM nowadays when you can go out and get the
    latest CD Rom game for about the same?  Most people don't pirate roms
    because they are too cheap, they do it because they may miss an old
    game that you could no longer purchase even if you wanted to.

    4.  Is storing/distributing ROM images illigal?
      It may not nessisarily be illigal, it is more up to the person who
    downloads the image then the person who provides it.  It is a 
    questionable practice, and I wouldn't recomend it.  Even though you
    may see various web pages and FTP sites doing it, that doesn't make
    it legal.


@Endnode
@Node Installation " -„ū„- How 2 A/NES -„ū„- "


        Installation
        ------------

        Copy the nintendo.font into your FONTS: assign and copy 
	the rest of the files to a suitable directory.
        Ta-da! :)

	An installation script will probably be added later
	for this purpose...

@Endnode
@Node Future " -„ū„- The future of A/NES -„ū„- "


        The future
        ----------


        Bugfixes           - For example, the 6502 emulation is not
                             perfect yet. And there is still some
			     stuff that isn't emulated yet...

        More Speed         - Who cares about hardware limits? :)

        MMC/Mapper support - Many games uses them...

        Joystick 2         - Yes. 2 players at the same time is
                             soon possible... :)

        Sound              - This one has got a low priority right now.
                             First we want to make the emulation work
                             as stable as possible.

        Zapper support     - How about playing "Duck Hunt" with your
                             mouse instead of a lightgun? :)
                             Don't know for sure if this is 100%
                             possible yet though...

        GameGenie/AR       - What is a game without a good cheat? :)



@Endnode
